Heat the vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir onions in the saucepan for 20 minutes. Mix in the beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, and black pepper. Bring to a boil; remove from heat. Preheat the oven broiler. Arrange bread slices on a baking sheet, and sprinkle with cheese. Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for about 1 minute or until cheese is melted and golden. Ladle soup into 6 bowls. Top each serving with a slice of the toasted bread.